### Floating (Zero-G)

No gravity, no ground contact. Motion is purely inertial—constant velocity, small corrective pulses.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'floater
    (shape 'circle 20)
    (color 180 200 220))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((pulse? (= (modulo t 60) 0))
             (x (+ 100 (* t 2)))
             (y (+ 240 (* 0.3 (sin (* t 0.05))))))
        (entity 'floater (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A pale blue circle drifts. Tiny sinusoidal drift (0.3-pixel amplitude) suggests breathing or micro-adjustments. No bobs, no weight—pure float.]

The sine is so shallow it's almost subliminal. That's the point.

