### Prowling

Slow, controlled, weight shifts exaggerated. Predator stalking prey.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'prowler
    (shape 'circle 24)
    (color 100 80 60))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((phase (modulo t 90))
             (x (+ 120 (* t 0.8)))
             (y (+ 310 (* 6 (sin (* phase (/ 3.14159 45))))))
             (crouch (if (< (modulo phase 45) 20) 4 0)))
        (entity 'prowler (at (+ x (* 2 (sin (* phase (/ 3.14159 45))))) (+ y crouch)))))))
```

[VISUAL: A brown circle prowls. Slow forward motion (0.8 pixels/tick). Each step involves a crouch (4 pixels down for 20 ticks) and a horizontal sway (±2 pixels). Tense, deliberate.]

The crouch is a discrete state, not a smooth ramp—models the \"load the spring\" moment before each step.

