### Soaring

Wings extended, gliding. Slow descent, occasional flap to regain altitude.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'soarer
    (shape 'circle 22)
    (color 200 200 220))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((flap-cycle (modulo t 120))
             (flapping? (< flap-cycle 10))
             (x (+ 100 (* t 3)))
             (y (if flapping?
                    (- 200 (* flap-cycle 2))
                    (+ 200 (* (- flap-cycle 10) 0.3)))))
        (entity 'soarer (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A white circle soars. Every 120 ticks it flaps (10 ticks, sharp ascent), then glides (110 ticks, slow descent). The sawtooth profile is characteristic of soaring birds.]

The glide is a gentle linear descent. The flap is a sharp reversal.

