### Tumbling

Uncontrolled rotation, chaotic trajectory. Falling through space.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'tumbler
    (shape 'circle 20)
    (color 160 140 120))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((x (+ 200 (* 40 (sin (* t 0.1)))))
             (y (+ 100 (* t 1.5)))
             (angle (* t 7)))
        (entity 'tumbler
          (at x y)
          (turn angle))))))
```

[VISUAL: A tan circle tumbles downward, spinning fast (7° per tick) while oscillating horizontally (sine wave). Chaotic, uncontrolled.]

The horizontal sine and the spin are unrelated—no phase lock. That's what makes it feel random.

