### Wheeling

Circular path, constant speed. Orbiting a center.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'wheeler
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 140 180 140))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((angle (* t 0.05))
             (cx 240)
             (cy 240)
             (radius 80)
             (x (+ cx (* radius (cos angle))))
             (y (+ cy (* radius (sin angle)))))
        (entity 'wheeler (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A green circle orbits a fixed center point (240, 240) at radius 80. Smooth, even speed. The circle traces a perfect orbit.]

Polar coordinates: angle advances linearly, position computed from center + radius × (cos, sin).

