### Figure-Eight

A Lissajous curve: two perpendicular oscillations with a 2:1 frequency ratio.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'eight
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 180 140 200))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((x (+ 240 (* 60 (sin (* t 0.05)))))
             (y (+ 240 (* 60 (sin (* t 0.1))))))
        (entity 'eight (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A purple circle traces a figure-eight. The x-oscillation is half the frequency of y, so the path crosses itself at the center. Hypnotic, looping.]

Lissajous figures arise whenever two harmonic motions interact. Here, 1:2 ratio = figure-eight.

