### Spiraling In

Circular motion with decreasing radius. Prey circling the drain.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'spiraler
    (shape 'circle 16)
    (color 200 100 100))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((angle (* t 0.1))
             (radius (max 10 (- 120 (* t 0.5))))
             (cx 240)
             (cy 240)
             (x (+ cx (* radius (cos angle))))
             (y (+ cy (* radius (sin angle)))))
        (entity 'spiraler (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A red circle spirals inward toward center (240, 240). Radius shrinks from 120 to 10 over 220 ticks. The path is a tightening coil.]

The `max` clamps radius at 10 to prevent collapse to a point (which might cause jitter if cos/sin amplify floating-point error at tiny scales).

