### Spiraling Out

The inverse: radius increases, circle escapes.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'expander
    (shape 'circle 16)
    (color 100 200 180))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((angle (* t 0.08))
             (radius (+ 20 (* t 0.6)))
             (cx 240)
             (cy 240)
             (x (+ cx (* radius (cos angle))))
             (y (+ cy (* radius (sin angle)))))
        (entity 'expander (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A teal circle spirals outward from center. Radius grows 0.6 pixels/tick. The path uncoils into infinite space.]

If the canvas is finite, the circle eventually leaves the viewport—locomotion into the void.

