### Chain Locomotion

Multiple entities follow a leader, each delayed by a fixed number of ticks. A conga line.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'leader
    (shape 'circle 20)
    (color 220 80 60))
  (actor 'follower1
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 200 100 80))
  (actor 'follower2
    (shape 'circle 16)
    (color 180 120 100))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((leader-x (+ 100 (* 60 (sin (* t 0.02)))))
             (leader-y (+ 240 (* 40 (cos (* t 0.02)))))
             (t1 (max 0 (- t 20)))
             (f1-x (+ 100 (* 60 (sin (* t1 0.02)))))
             (f1-y (+ 240 (* 40 (cos (* t1 0.02)))))
             (t2 (max 0 (- t 40)))
             (f2-x (+ 100 (* 60 (sin (* t2 0.02)))))
             (f2-y (+ 240 (* 40 (cos (* t2 0.02))))))
        (entity 'leader (at leader-x leader-y))
        (entity 'follower1 (at f1-x f1-y))
        (entity 'follower2 (at f2-x f2-y))))))
```

[VISUAL: Three circles orbit. The leader (red, largest) traces a path. Follower1 (orange) is 20 ticks behind. Follower2 (tan, smallest) is 40 ticks behind. They form a chain, each retracing the leader's exact path with a lag.]

The followers use `(- t delay)` to sample the leader's trajectory in the past. They converge on the leader's current position as delay → 0.

