### Steering Toward Target

Entity adjusts heading each tick to aim toward a fixed point, then moves forward.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'seeker
    (shape 'circle 20)
    (color 100 180 100))
  (world
    (let ((sx 100) (sy 100) (heading 0))
      (on-tick
        (lambda (t)
          (let* ((target-x 400)
                 (target-y 300)
                 (dx (- target-x sx))
                 (dy (- target-y sy))
                 (desired-heading (atan dy dx))
                 (turn-rate 0.05)
                 (new-heading (+ heading (* turn-rate (- desired-heading heading))))
                 (speed 2)
                 (new-sx (+ sx (* speed (cos new-heading))))
                 (new-sy (+ sy (* speed (sin new-heading)))))
            (set! sx new-sx)
            (set! sy new-sy)
            (set! heading new-heading)
            (entity 'seeker (at sx sy) (turn (* heading 57.2958))))))))
```

*[needs: world-scoped state in motion]*

<!-- BUILD: motion needs world-scoped mutable state for steering/AI locomotion; currently on-tick lambda is stateless per invocation -->

If world-scoped mutation is unavailable, we mark the gap. Steering requires memory of heading and position across ticks.

