### Path Following

Entity follows a pre-defined spline or waypoint list.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'follower
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 200 120 60))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((waypoints '((100 . 100) (200 . 150) (300 . 120) (400 . 200)))
             (segment-duration 60)
             (total-duration (* segment-duration (- (length waypoints) 1)))
             (clamped-t (modulo t total-duration))
             (segment (quotient clamped-t segment-duration))
             (local-t (modulo clamped-t segment-duration))
             (progress (/ local-t segment-duration))
             (p0 (list-ref waypoints segment))
             (p1 (list-ref waypoints (+ segment 1)))
             (x (+ (car p0) (* progress (- (car p1) (car p0)))))
             (y (+ (cdr p0) (* progress (- (cdr p1) (cdr p0))))))
        (entity 'follower (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: An orange circle moves from waypoint to waypoint, linearly interpolating between each pair over 60 ticks. The path is a piecewise-linear route: (100,100) → (200,150) → (300,120) → (400,200), then loops.]

Each segment is one linear interpolation. Concatenate them to get a full path.

---


### Variable Speed Along Path

Same path, but speed modulated by a function—slow around corners, fast on straightaways.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'racer
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 180 60 60))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((waypoints '((100 . 100) (200 . 150) (300 . 120) (400 . 200)))
             (segment-duration-base 60)
             (segment (modulo (quotient t segment-duration-base) (- (length waypoints) 1)))
             (local-t (modulo t segment-duration-base))
             (corner? (or (= segment 1) (= segment 2)))
             (speed-mult (if corner? 0.6 1.2))
             (adjusted-duration (/ segment-duration-base speed-mult))
             (progress (/ local-t adjusted-duration))
             (clamped-progress (min 1.0 progress))
             (p0 (list-ref waypoints segment))
             (p1 (list-ref waypoints (+ segment 1)))
             (x (+ (car p0) (* clamped-progress (- (car p1) (car p0)))))
             (y (+ (cdr p0) (* clamped-progress (- (cdr p1) (cdr p0))))))
        (entity 'racer (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A red circle races the same path, but slows down 40% on segments 1 and 2 (corners) and speeds up 20% elsewhere. The rhythm is uneven—fast, slow, slow, fast.]

This is basic speed variation. Real racing lines involve easing and look-ahead.

