### Jumping Over Gap

Entity runs, detects edge, jumps, lands on far side.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'jumper
    (shape 'circle 20)
    (color 220 180 60))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((x (+ 80 (* t 2.5)))
             (gap-start 220)
             (gap-end 300)
             (over-gap? (and (> x gap-start) (< x gap-end)))
             (y (if over-gap?
                    (- 300 (* 40 (sin (* (- x gap-start) (/ 3.14159 (- gap-end gap-start))))))
                    320)))
        (entity 'jumper (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A yellow circle runs along y=320. At x=220 it jumps (arc peaks at 40 pixels above baseline), lands at x=300, continues running. The arc spans exactly the gap width.]

The jump is triggered by position, not time. The arc is a sine wave scaled to fit the gap.

