### Landing with Impact

Jump, but on landing we add a squash frame.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'lander
    (shape 'circle 22)
    (color 200 100 80))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((cycle (modulo t 80))
             (x (+ 100 (* (quotient t 80) 100) (* cycle 1.25)))
             (jumping? (and (> cycle 20) (< cycle 50)))
             (landing? (and (>= cycle 50) (< cycle 56)))
             (y (cond
                  (jumping? (- 300 (* 35 (sin (* (- cycle 20) (/ 3.14159 30))))))
                  (landing? (+ 320 (* (- cycle 50) 0.8)))
                  (else 320))))
        (entity 'lander (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: An orange circle runs and jumps every 80 ticks. On landing (frames 50–56), it compresses downward (sinks ~5 pixels) before bouncing back. The compression is linear, the release is instant. Feels like knees buckling.]

The landing squash is a ramp, not a bounce. It dissipates energy.

