### Double Jump

Jump, then jump again in mid-air. Video-game logic.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'double-jumper
    (shape 'circle 20)
    (color 140 100 200))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((cycle (modulo t 100))
             (first-jump? (and (> cycle 10) (< cycle 30)))
             (second-jump? (and (> cycle 35) (< cycle 55)))
             (x (+ 100 (* t 2)))
             (y1 (if first-jump?
                     (- 300 (* 25 (sin (* (- cycle 10) (/ 3.14159 20)))))
                     320))
             (y2 (if second-jump?
                     (- y1 (* 20 (sin (* (- cycle 35) (/ 3.14159 20)))))
                     y1))
             (y y2))
        (entity 'double-jumper (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A purple circle runs, jumps (arc 1), then—while still in the first arc—jumps again (arc 2, smaller, stacked on top). The second jump adds height mid-air. Non-physical, expressive.]

The second jump is computed as an offset from the first. They compose.

