### Wall Jump

Hit a wall, reverse horizontal velocity, jump upward.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'wall-jumper
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 180 60 100))
  (world
    (let ((vx 3) (vy 0) (px 100) (py 300))
      (on-tick
        (lambda (t)
          (let* ((wall-x 400)
                 (hit-wall? (and (> vx 0) (>= px wall-x)))
                 (new-vx (if hit-wall? (* vx -1) vx))
                 (new-vy (if hit-wall? -5 (min 5 (+ vy 0.2))))
                 (new-px (+ px new-vx))
                 (new-py (+ py new-vy)))
            (set! vx new-vx)
            (set! vy new-vy)
            (set! px new-px)
            (set! py new-py)
            (entity 'wall-jumper (at px py))))))))
```

*[needs: world-scoped mutable state]*

<!-- BUILD: wall-jump needs mutable velocity state across ticks; currently blocked by stateless on-tick -->

Placeholder showing the logic. On wall collision, `vx` flips and `vy` becomes negative (upward impulse).

