### Grappling Hook Swing

Fire hook, attach to anchor point, swing in pendulum arc.

*Complex—needs vector math, constraint solving. Mark as advanced example.*

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'swinger
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 100 140 100))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((anchor-x 240)
             (anchor-y 100)
             (rope-length 120)
             (angle (+ 0.5 (* 0.6 (sin (* t 0.05)))))
             (x (+ anchor-x (* rope-length (sin angle))))
             (y (+ anchor-y (* rope-length (cos angle)))))
        (entity 'swinger (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A green circle swings beneath a fixed anchor point (240, 100). The angle oscillates ±0.6 radians in a sine wave. The motion is a pendulum arc. Simplified—real swing needs angular acceleration and damping.]

True pendulum physics: `θ'' = -(g/L) sin θ`. Here we fake it with a sine wave. Close enough for feel.

