### Zip Line

Slide along a diagonal cable from high anchor to low anchor.

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'slider
    (shape 'circle 18)
    (color 200 180 60))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((start-x 100)
             (start-y 150)
             (end-x 400)
             (end-y 320)
             (duration 120)
             (progress (min 1.0 (/ (modulo t duration) duration)))
             (x (+ start-x (* progress (- end-x start-x))))
             (y (+ start-y (* progress (- end-y start-y)))))
        (entity 'slider (at x y))))))
```

[VISUAL: A yellow circle slides from (100,150) to (400,320) over 120 ticks, then resets. The path is a straight diagonal line. Gravity would make it accelerate; here it's linear for simplicity.]

Add easing (quadratic) to model gravity-assisted acceleration.

