### Rolling Down Slope

Circle rolls (rotates) while descending a slope. Rotation speed matches linear speed (no slip).

```scheme
(motion
  (actor 'roller
    (shape 'circle 24)
    (color 160 120 80))
  (on-tick
    (lambda (t)
      (let* ((x (+ 100 (* t 2)))
             (slope 0.3)
             (y (+ 200 (* x slope)))
             (radius 24)
             (distance-traveled (* t 2))
             (angle (* (/ distance-traveled radius) 57.2958)))
        (entity 'roller
          (at x y)
          (turn angle))))))
```

[VISUAL: A brown circle rolls down a slope (y increases as x increases). The circle rotates as it moves—angle is `distance / radius`, converted to degrees. No slip. Feels physically grounded.]

The rotation rate is exact: arc length = radius × angle (in radians).

